text: Sir George Houston Reid (25 February 1845 â€“ 12 September 1918) was the fourth Prime Minister of Australia. He was the first Leader of the Opposition and leader of Free Trade Party. He moved to London after he retired and was elected to the House of Commons. Reid was elected to the Australian Paliament in 1901 for the Division of East Sydney. He retired in 1910.
